nuary 2018Kostas Axelos traces his thinking on the world deployed as play from Heraclitus through to the culmination of metaphysical philosophy with Nietzsche, Marx and Heidegger.Originally published in 1969, Le Jeu du Monde, conceives of the dawn of the 21st-century in which technological transformations coincide with an increased world at play. Are we continually falling when we are continually scrolling? Are we homeless on our homepages and playless at our PlayStations? Axelos demands a future thinking of fragmentary wholeness where humans – global players and worldwide gamers of planetary and wordless worlds – have yet to learn to play the play of the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhilosophy, Greek (Modern). 0aPlay (Philosophy). 4aPhilosophy. 7aCOMPUTERS / Information Theory.2bisacsh1 aClemens, Justin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClemens, Justin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMonz, Hellmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonz, Hellmut, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131912408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023z9783111318165oZDB-23-DEI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107976400 cprintz978147444906940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474449083?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474449083423Co